Title: Global Holdout
Main Problem (To Solve): Data Science cannot measure the total impact of features delivered in a period
Description: Define a Holdout Group which doesn't receive any new feature for a certain amount of time (usually a quarter)
Outcome/Goal: Measure the total impact of all features rollout in a certain amount of time (usually a quarter)

Title: Feature Impact Monitoring

Outcome/Goal: Being able to measure impact of the RTP/Feature through the stages of progressive rollout

Title: Experiments Bank - MVP
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners have no centralized repository to discover and learn from past experiments, leading to duplicated efforts, missed learnings, inconsistent practices, and lost institutional knowledge.
Description: Create an Experiment Library where Experiment Owners can explore & learn & and get inspired from all past Experiments ran in different areas of the product. An Experiment item will have the Hypothesis, Owner, Experiment Metadata, Details and Experiment resoning, Pictures, Results & Insights.
Outcome/Goal: Enable Experiment Owners to learn from past Experiments insights in order to create new ones which can bring more value to our users.

Title: Content Experimentation - MVP
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners relys on Engineering to build simple design experiment.
Description:
Create a functionality where Experiment Owner can create a Content Experiment where they can modify the Ui Elements of specific Ui Component such a Widget, Popup, Pane. Among the things that they can change are: Text, Fonts, Colors, Icons, Page Arrengamgent, Buttons without the need of Engineering or little need but keeping in the alignment of Express Design Guidelines.
They should be able to preview the new Variants.
Outcome/Goal: Enable Experiment Owners to run fast multiple Content Experiments by empowering them to design fast multiple Experiment variants with no or little Engineering effort.

Title: Traffic Lanes - Phase 1 - Foundations & Conflict Management - MVP
Main Problem (To Solve):
Experiment owners cannot run more multiple experiments simultaneously in the same product area due to traffic allocation constraints, limiting experimentation velocity and platform scalability, 

Experiment owners don't know which lanes are available to avoid conflicts.
Description:
Split the traffic in multiple lanes (eg. 5) all having a sample of the population. Allowing for multiple experiment to run in parrallel in the same product area.  

Implement a logic for the Traffic Lanes to avoid Experimentation conflict such as running on the same Product area, KPIs, etc.
Outcome/Goal:
Scale the Experiments that can run simulatinously in the same area reducing the conflicts.

Expand the traffic lanes usage and so, the experiments running in parallel.

Title: Experimentation on Services

Title: AEP Customer Profile Attributes
Main Problem (To Solve): The Experimentation Platform's reliance on slow services (APS, UDC) prevents advanced cross-product segmentation (Acrobat - Express) and impacts app performance.
Description:
Integrate the platform with AEP Customer 365 and expose the Customer Profile segmentation in Horizon Platform.
Also, make this consumable by Agents
Outcome/Goal:
Expand Segmentation capabilities and reduce the performance issues due to APS, UDC and other slow services.
In the end, other tenants may join and use our platform.

Title: Knowledge Bot
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners spend a lot of time manually extracting information from multiple experiments and consolidating them into valuable insights for future experiments.
Description:
Create an Experimentation Conversational Bot which can give users general information about Experimentations.
1. This can extract information from the experiment Bank knowledge
2. Offer information about overall experiments results
3. Experimentation Platform capabilities (similar to singularity)
Outcome/Goal: Reduce the time for users to search and learn about experimentation and the experiments ran in the platform

Title: Experimentation on Settings
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners need to develop multiple feature flags for Multi Variant Experiments where they want to validate multiple options.
Description: Expand experiments variants from feature flagging to options allowing each variant to have a set of options. Each option can have different alfa numeric values. Minimizing the number of feature flags developers need to define in code in order o create a MultiVariant Test. Eg. An Experiment which wants to test 3 different texts and 3 Icons will need only 2 Options (Icon, TextLabel)
Outcome/Goal: Reduce the code complexity for multi variant experiments and time to develop multi variant experiments

Title: Traffic calculator
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners don't know how much time an experiment will take in order to be statistically valid.
Description: Calculate the necessary traffic & time for an experiment based on the number of variants
Outcome/Goal: Create visibility for the Experiment owner for how long the Experiment will need to be run in order to get to have trusted results

Title: Intelligent traffic calculator
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners don't know how much time an experiment will take in order to be statistically valid.
Description: Calculate the necessary traffic & time for an experiment based on the number of variants and tested area traffic.
Outcome/Goal: Create visibility for the Experiment owner for how long the Experiment will need to be run in order to get to have trusted results

Objective: Minimize the negative end user impact
Title: Intelligent traffic allocation
Main Problem (To Solve): Muli variant tests takes an unecessary long time while end users are exposed for a long period of time to unsuccessfull experiments.
Description: Implement Advanced dynamic traffic allocation such as: Multi-armed Bandit, Bayesian.
Outcome/Goal: Reduce the time for running an experiment especially the Multi Variant Tests

Title: Allow multiple properties for exposure event
Main Problem (To Solve): Data Science needs to do additional filtering in order to analysis on the Experiment and it will decrease the use of Automatic Dashboard
Description: Being able to define multiple properties per exposure event
Outcome/Goal: Enable more complex Experiment to utilize automated reporting that is being developed requiring View Experiment as a starting point.

Objective: Minimize the negative end user impact
Title: Experiment simulation
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners loose time to full run invalid experiments impacting end users users and increasing the learning time.
Description: Build 100k Agents that behave as users in the App and test the variations in a dry environment so, Experimentation owners can validate fast an experiment upfront sending it to users.
Outcome/Goal: Iterate rapidly and learn from both positive and negative results without impacting users

Title: Conversational advanced reporting analysis
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners and data science may require advanced report analysis for complex experiments with uncertain results.
Description:
Implement a bot that can answer to advanced reporting questions on an Experiment such as:
1. What is the traffic source distribution on my experiment variants
2. What the traffic distribution based on country on my variants
3. Draw a funnel of my traffic that exported my experiment.
This bot can add the results in the dashboard.
Outcome/Goal: Reduce the Data Science effort to do advanced analysis of an experiment.

Title: Experiments Design & Insights

Description: Create a system that consolidates the experiment information and insights that can be furthered consumed by Agents. This should know the: Experiment Designs, Hypothesis, Platform Area, Team, Variants, Problems to solve and the results together with the learnings from it.
Outcome/Goal: Create a memory consumable by Agents about the Experiments history

Title: Hypothesis generator
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners hardly leverage past experiments insights into the new hypothesis due to the complexity of searching and aligning learnings with their goals.

Title: Conversational experiment configuration
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners rarely configure experiments for specific audiance and lower traffic.
Description:
Support the Experiment Owner to configure the experiment by setting up the segmentation, necessary traffic percentage and exposure event.
Features:
1. Provide information the different experiment configuration.
2. Free text segmentation to configued segmentation.
3. Traffic % allocation and lane allocation suggestion.
Outcome/Goal: Support Experiment owners to configure experimentats minimazing the traffic space and maximazing the possible valuable and learnings of an experiment.

Title: Form redesign
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners find it difficult to discover and configure experiment settings as the creation form has become cumbersone to navigate due to platform feature growth.
Description: We need a redesign of the Experimentation form to improve the User Flows as the Experimentation engine has increased in complexity
Outcome/Goal: Improve the user flow and discoverability of the features

Title: Singularity Exp Bot Dashboard
Main Problem (To Solve): The platform lacks a monitoring dashboard for their Conversational Bots
Description: Create a monitoring dashboard of the Singularity bot to monitor how well the bot responded. + Benchmark
Outcome/Goal: A dashboard from where we can monitor the answers and the bot quality and take insights for future improvements.

Objective: Minimize the negative end user impact
Title: Gradual experiment ramp up
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners lack automated controls for gradual experiment ramp up, forcing them to either launch to full populations immediately or manually adjust traffic daily without proper monitoring mechanisms.
Description:
Implement a mechanism that allows Experiment Owners to gradually ramp up an experiment until the full set population
1. First few hours run an A/A to check the experiment health
2. Next few hours ramp up the test to 25% to check the experiment health and the variant kpi health.
3. Next few hours ramp up the test to 50% to check the experiment health and the variant KPI health
4. Next few hours ramp up the test to 100% to check the experiment health and the variant KPI health
Outcome/Goal: Reduce the possible negative impact of a negative or buggy experiment

Title: Fullstory Session Tracking Integration
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners don't levrage the session trackings information when they take Experimentation decisions.
Description: Extract the users sessions information for Agents. Can be a direct integration, Vector DB or an MCP server.
Outcome/Goal: Enhance the Agents knowledge also with the user session tracking analysis

Title: Combinatorial variant generator
Main Problem (To Solve): Experiment owners spend time manually creating all variant combinations when configuring multi-variate experiments with multiple feature flags, which is time-consuming and error-prone.
Outcome/Goal: Reduce the time configure an experiment
